search:nestjs+grpc:nestjs grpc transport.content:
- Install NestJS gRPC transporter: `npm install @grpc/grpc-js @grpc/proto-loader`
- Define gRPC service methods using `.proto` files.
- Use the `@GrpcMethod` decorator to map gRPC methods in NestJS controllers.
- Update your module to include the gRPC transport.
- Example of a `.proto` file:
  ```proto
  syntax = "proto3";
  package user;

  service UserService {
    rpc GetUser (GetUserRequest) returns (GetUserResponse);
  }

  message GetUserRequest {
    string id = 1;
  }

  message GetUserResponse {
    string name = 1;
    int32 age = 2;
  }
  ```
- Implement the gRPC method in your service:
  ```typescript
  @GrpcMethod('UserService', 'GetUser')
  async getUser(data: GetUserRequest, metadata: Metadata): Promise<GetUserResponse> {
    // Implementation here
  }
  ```
- Ensure NestJS is configured to use the gRPC transport in `app.module.ts`.
